name: Skagit Valley College Oak Harbor Campus
directions: It's in the building with the registration/student services/financial aid offices. You walk in, go all the way downstairs, hang a right and go to the end of the hallway. It's a multi-stall all-gender bathroom on the left at the end of the hall.
comment: I found it on accident once when I was trying to find the book store and I've been using it ever since. I've used this bathroom a million times and haven't EVER seen another person in it. I honestly don't think very many people even know about it because it's one of the bathrooms that hasn't gotten remodeled yet. It's really cool too. If you get a chance, look out the window. The window is almost level with the ground outside. Anyways, have fun, and be safe! <3

name: Warren Hunting Smith Library, HWS Colleges
directions: Safe and accessible bathrooms are located on the first floor of the actual library (not the ones in the lobby).  Once through the doors of the library, walk straight back past the IT Desk.  Turn right down the hallway that is just past the printers.  After the glass-walled room on your left, there will be two bathrooms, one on either side.  These bathrooms are single stall, gender free/gender neutral, and accessible to all.
